2008-04-29 06:41:24 Source: Xinhua News AgencyHo Chi Minh City, April 28 (Reporters: Fei Honghai, Huang Haimin) "Just like their fellow countrymen at home, overseas students also eagerly look forward to the arrival of the Olympic torch."This is how four representatives of Chinese students in Ho Chi Minh City expressed their mind in an interview with the reporters of Xinhua News Agency.They are all studying in the University of Social and Human Sciences in Ho Chi Minh City.They said that, after learning that the Olympic torch would pass through Ho Chi Minh City, the Chinese students began making preparations in early April. They first asked about whether their university had arranged any relevant activity and then contacted the Chinese consulate-general in Ho Chi Minh City expressing the hope of taking part in the relay.There are more than 100 Chinese students in Ho Chi Minh City.They designed various plans for welcoming the Olympic torch. For instance, they would wear the same cloths during the relay and hold high a banner that said "Chinese Students Embracing Olympic Torch" or run alongside the torch bearers.Tang Minmin, one of the representatives, said: "We are very excited to welcome the arrival of the Olympic torch in a foreign country.A classmate of mine was sleepless for two nights after learning that the Olympic torch would pass through Ho Chi Minh City.""Many of our Vietnamese classmates are just as excited and hope that we can take them along to witness the relay," said Qin Xinzi.Tang Li and Cun Xiao showed several small five-star flags they had made to the reporters, saying: "Though we may be able to attend only one of the three events, we hope to express our patriotic zeal in our own way.That zeal must be expressed."Ho Chi Minh City will see the arrival of the Olympic torch on 28th. On the afternoon of 29th, 60 torch bearers will cover the 1013km journey while holding the torch.